main event: On December 9, 1964, radar operators at Patuxent River, Maryland, tracked unidentified flying objects that exhibited unusual radar signatures.
interesting points: Radar operators observed multiple radar targets moving at high speeds estimated between 60,000-65,000 knots per hour., The targets were tracked for up to 48 seconds before fading from the radar., Investigation revealed that initial radar returns were caused by a flock of birds, not unidentified aircraft., No simultaneous data was recorded by other radar locations, indicating the returns were unique to this site., The Air Force eventually concluded that the targets were likely an electronic anomaly or interference rather than extraterrestrial objects.
witness description: radar operators from the Naval Air Station
